<doc id="400811" wikidata="Q4116478" url="?curid=400811" title="Nabatieh refugee camp">
<text>Nabatieh refugee camp was a Palestinian refugee camp in southern Lebanon. Established in 1956 by UNRWA, the camp was destroyed by Israel in 1974. Conducted as a retaliation for the Ma&#x27;alot massacre, the Israeli bombing of the camp killed 27-50 people and injured 100-184.

The 1974 film &quot;They Do Not Exist&quot; by Palestinian filmmaker Mustafa Abu Ali documents the destruction of the camp.

